REGULAR 4-POLYTOPES (SCHLÄFLI SYMBOLS)
=====================================================================
516.15 (Geometry in four dimensions)
Schläfli symbol: {p, q, r}
Meaning:
  - Cells are {p, q} polyhedra
  - r cells meet around each edge

List of the six regular 4-polytopes:
  5-cell (4-simplex)        : {3, 3, 3}
  8-cell (tesseract)        : {4, 3, 3}
  16-cell                   : {3, 3, 4}
  24-cell                   : {3, 4, 3}
  120-cell                  : {5, 3, 3}
  600-cell                  : {3, 3, 5}

Duality:
  Dual({p, q, r}) = {r, q, p}

=====================================================================

Tesseract {4,3,3}:
  V = 16
  E = 32
  F = 24   (square faces)
  C = 8    (cubic cells)

600-cell {3,3,5}:
  V = 120
  E = 720
  F = 1200 (triangular faces)
  C = 600  (tetrahedral cells)

General regular 4-polytope formulas (schematic):
  Let G = symmetry group order of the polytope.
  Then counts follow:
    V = G / |Stab(vertex)|
    E = G / |Stab(edge)|
    F = G / |Stab(face)|
    C = G / |Stab(cell)|

